reviewText: A must-see! Inward Hunger is a treasure chest for history enthusiasts in the Caribbean and worldwide filled with never before seen archive footage, photos, interviews and more!

Inward Hunger is a very well directed, extensively researched and honest take on the life of the one of the greatest men in modern history. I wish this film existed when I was studying for CXC history, maybe then I would have gotten a distinction.
Magnificent Documentary! Eric Williams is a Inspiration Beyond Words! I wish More Trinidadian & West Indian Youth would Study this Man's History and Sincerely Experience the De-Colonialize Mind!
A thorough and well-researched series that gives genuine insights into the first prime minister of Trinidad and Tobago.
